113
00:11:39,863 --> 00:11:42,183
- You got it.
- Sure, I did.

114
00:11:45,543 --> 00:11:47,583
Yeah, this is Kate Lloyd.

115
00:11:48,703 --> 00:11:51,104
- Columbia paleontology.
- Welcome.

116
00:11:51,184 --> 00:11:53,024
Adam Finch,
my research assistant.

117
00:11:53,104 --> 00:11:54,344
- Welcome.
- Hi.

118
00:11:54,464 --> 00:11:55,944
This is Edvard, my good friend.

119
00:11:56,024 --> 00:11:59,544
This is some of my team.
Karl and Juliette. Both geologists.

120
00:11:59,624 --> 00:12:01,104
- Hi.
- Welcome.

121
00:12:02,224 --> 00:12:03,504
Okay.

122
00:12:03,944 --> 00:12:07,104
Let me show you why you flew
10,000 miles.

123
00:12:45,788 --> 00:12:47,268
Holy shit!

124
00:12:48,268 --> 00:12:51,988
We estimated this has been here
approximately 100,000 years.

125
00:12:52,548 --> 00:12:55,508
We picked up a signal transmitting.

126
00:12:56,988 --> 00:12:59,188
Some kind of distress call, perhaps.

127
00:12:59,988 --> 00:13:01,388
Incredible.

128
00:13:01,508 --> 00:13:03,349
We think the signal
was triggered

129
00:13:03,429 --> 00:13:06,549
when the survivor
exited the craft.

130
00:13:09,909 --> 00:13:11,469
Survivor?

131
00:13:35,351 --> 00:13:36,711
My God.

132
00:13:52,712 --> 00:13:55,432
How long will it take to get it out,
do you know, Kate?

133
00:13:58,393 --> 00:14:00,993
Assuming you've the right equipment,
I'd say...

134
00:14:02,073 --> 00:14:03,673
maybe half a day.

135
00:14:04,713 --> 00:14:06,073
Good.

136
00:14:26,515 --> 00:14:30,035
The ice, should I ask you how fragile
is it?

137
00:14:30,115 --> 00:14:31,915
It's not in a fracture zone.

138
00:14:31,995 --> 00:14:34,756
So there's very little risk of fissuring.

139
00:14:34,836 --> 00:14:36,516
And the ice is quite dense.

140
00:14:36,596 --> 00:14:39,116
So we think
we can get it out in one piece.

141
00:14:39,196 --> 00:14:40,516
Good.

142
00:14:40,636 --> 00:14:43,556
I mean, rough estimates about
6 by 12 feet, 3 and a half feet high.

143
00:14:43,636 --> 00:14:45,916
- Probably some place right around...
- That's great...

144
00:14:45,996 --> 00:14:49,556
Make sure that everyone stays off
the radio.

145
00:14:49,636 --> 00:14:51,676
I do not want any information out.

146
00:14:51,756 --> 00:14:54,757
And the crane... do we have
something appropriate for this?

147
00:14:55,117 --> 00:14:57,597
Yes, it's already there.
It's all set up.

148
00:14:57,717 --> 00:14:58,997
I'm Peder, by the way.

149
00:14:59,117 --> 00:15:00,877
- Peder.
- Nice to meet you.

150
00:15:00,957 --> 00:15:04,637
So, you've gotten it all taken care of.
I don't think you really need me.

151
00:15:04,917 --> 00:15:07,877
What about him?
He's secretly disinterested or...?

152
00:15:07,997 --> 00:15:09,237
Oh, that's Lars.

153
00:15:09,317 --> 00:15:11,999
He does not understand English,
but he works like a bear.

154
00:15:12,119 --> 00:15:13,539
And, as you can see
from the scans,

155
00:15:13,540 --> 00:15:16,740
the ship carved a 200 meter tunnel
into the ice.

156
00:15:18,359 --> 00:15:21,879
So, let me get this right.
You crashed into a glacier...

157
00:15:22,599 --> 00:15:24,279
