we have to take it from here to here.

166
00:17:20,048 --> 00:17:21,888
Start with 4 inches.

167
00:17:22,288 --> 00:17:24,168
I never believed in this shit.

168
00:17:25,008 --> 00:17:26,808
I always did.

169
00:17:28,408 --> 00:17:31,088
- We're all set?
- Nearly there.

170
00:17:31,208 --> 00:17:32,728
Good.

171
00:17:33,248 --> 00:17:34,688
Good.

172
00:17:37,248 --> 00:17:40,929
But before we do,
I'm going to take a tissue sample.

173
00:17:44,049 --> 00:17:46,249
Do you really that's a good idea?

174
00:17:47,329 --> 00:17:49,049
Yes, I do.

175
00:17:50,169 --> 00:17:52,209
I mean the conditions
are so unpredictable

176
00:17:52,289 --> 00:17:54,209
and we don't have the proper equipment.

177
00:17:54,329 --> 00:17:55,929
Sterilization is an issue.

178
00:17:56,049 --> 00:17:59,571
Edvard, what do you have in the way of
a small diameter drill?

179
00:17:59,691 --> 00:18:01,811
Up to 30mm.

180
00:18:02,291 --> 00:18:03,971
Very good.

181
00:18:04,331 --> 00:18:06,651
I think somewhere around here.

182
00:18:11,011 --> 00:18:13,691
Kate.
Just a second.

183
00:18:15,212 --> 00:18:19,052
In the future, don't contradict me
in front of those people again.

184
00:18:19,172 --> 00:18:21,772
- I just thought...
- You're not here to think.

185
00:18:21,892 --> 00:18:24,412
You're here to get that thing
safe out of the ice.

186
00:18:25,932 --> 00:18:27,972
I hope we understand each other.

187
00:20:12,540 --> 00:20:14,940
So, have you ever tasted this before?

188
00:20:15,060 --> 00:20:17,020
- No, I haven't.
- It tastes very bad.

189
00:20:17,140 --> 00:20:19,540
Gentlemen.
Ladies.

190
00:20:19,860 --> 00:20:23,181
After a short but thorough investigation

191
00:20:23,301 --> 00:20:25,301
of our visitor,

192
00:20:25,981 --> 00:20:28,061
I can say, unequivocally,

193
00:20:28,381 --> 00:20:32,781
that I've never seen anything
on any cellular level,

194
00:20:34,701 --> 00:20:38,141
like what we have
in that other room.

195
00:20:38,421 --> 00:20:41,181
<i>Now, the impact of this find...</i>

196
00:20:41,261 --> 00:20:44,263
<i>will be felt
for thousands of years.</i>

197
00:20:44,503 --> 00:20:46,703
<i>From this point on,</i>

198
00:20:46,823 --> 00:20:50,943
<i>the world as we know it
has forever been altered.</i>

199
00:20:54,103 --> 00:20:57,263
You, my friends,
will all be immortalized,

200
00:20:57,343 --> 00:21:00,464
as the people
who made this discovery.

201
00:21:07,504 --> 00:21:08,984
Thank you.

202
00:21:14,264 --> 00:21:17,184
Do you think they're going to pay a bonus
for bringing over an alien

203
00:21:17,264 --> 00:21:19,025
instead of coal samples?

204
00:21:28,265 --> 00:21:30,945
You've got anything better than
this cough syrup?

205
00:21:31,505 --> 00:21:32,825
- Hey, Griggy.
- Yeah?

206
00:21:32,945 --> 00:21:35,065
You want to go out
and get the cabinet stash?

207
00:21:35,145 --> 00:21:36,667
Sure, no problem.

208
00:21:37,587 --> 00:21:38,907
I'm on it.

209
00:22:02,508 --> 00:22:04,468
Where did I put this bottle?

210
00:23:43,275 --> 00:23:44,796
Jesus Ch...

211
00:23:50,556 --> 00:23:52,236
Screw you, man.

212
00:23:54,676 --> 00:23:56,316
Son of a...

213
