to the military hospital.

255
00:31:09,678 --> 00:31:11,297
And what're you gonna tell them, hmm?

256
00:31:12,478 --> 00:31:16,828
I'm gonna tell them the truth, as crazy
as it sounds.

257
00:32:30,233 --> 00:32:32,873
Kate?
Can you help here?

258
00:32:38,355 --> 00:32:39,795
Come on.

259
00:32:43,835 --> 00:32:45,515
Pull that side up.

260
00:33:10,716 --> 00:33:14,437
His face is encased in some type
of amniotic sac.

261
00:33:40,479 --> 00:33:43,959
The tissue. Looks almost new.

262
00:33:46,719 --> 00:33:48,839
What was it doing to him?

263
00:33:49,639 --> 00:33:52,280
It appears that it was absorbing him.

264
00:33:52,880 --> 00:33:55,160
Some type of digestion.

265
00:33:56,000 --> 00:33:57,560
It's fascinating.

266
00:33:59,880 --> 00:34:01,640
<i>It is fascinating.</i>

267
00:34:17,791 --> 00:34:19,721
- What's the matter? Are you okay?
- I'm fine.

268
00:34:19,741 --> 00:34:21,441
- You sure?
- Yeah, I'm okay.

269
00:34:21,491 --> 00:34:24,121
- Do you need something?
- No, no. I'm okay.

270
00:34:50,764 --> 00:34:52,564
What is this?

271
00:34:54,404 --> 00:34:56,364
Looks like a titanium plate.

272
00:34:56,884 --> 00:35:00,044
Used to reinforce bones
and compound fractures.

273
00:35:00,164 --> 00:35:02,004
Yeah, that's right.

274
00:35:02,364 --> 00:35:04,485
Henrik broke his arm last year.

275
00:35:04,605 --> 00:35:07,445
He had to go to Argentina
to get it set.

276
00:35:11,085 --> 00:35:14,365
So if this was in his arm,
what's it doing out of him now?

277
00:35:18,885 --> 00:35:20,365
That's a good question.

278
00:35:39,647 --> 00:35:41,128
What are you doing?

279
00:35:41,608 --> 00:35:44,008
Took a sample of Henrik's tissue.

280
00:35:44,088 --> 00:35:47,248
I want to find out what this thing
was doing to him.

281
00:35:56,248 --> 00:35:58,609
I think you should take a look at this.

282
00:36:08,809 --> 00:36:11,009
These cells aren't dead.

283
00:36:12,929 --> 00:36:15,009
That's not possible.

284
00:36:19,891 --> 00:36:22,691
Looks like the alien cells
are somehow

285
00:36:22,771 --> 00:36:25,211
attacking Henrik's cells
and then they...

286
00:36:26,571 --> 00:36:28,531
What is that? It looks like
they are transforming...

287
00:36:28,651 --> 00:36:30,571
They're imitating his cells.

288
00:36:33,331 --> 00:36:35,532
Okay, I don't know
if that's what I'm seeing, but...

289
00:36:35,612 --> 00:36:37,452
They're imitating him.

290
00:37:03,533 --> 00:37:05,013
It's going to be okay, Olav.

291
00:37:05,093 --> 00:37:07,093
A doctor will see you in McMurdo.

292
00:37:09,413 --> 00:37:11,013
Kate.

293
00:37:12,055 --> 00:37:13,695
- Hey.
- Hi.

294
00:37:15,415 --> 00:37:16,775
We're leaving.

295
00:37:18,215 --> 00:37:20,325
Once the weather holds up,
we'll be back with help...

296
00:37:20,335 --> 00:37:22,415
as soon as we can.

297
00:37:22,975 --> 00:37:24,535
Okay.

298
00:37:25,695 --> 00:37:27,055
Alright.

299
00:37:39,216 --> 00:37:41,176
- Keep him warm.
- I will.

300
00:37:41,416 --> 00:37:42,936
C'mon, let's go.

301
00:37:47,936 --> 00:37:49,337
Sit down there.

302
00:37:50,577 --> 00:37:52,257
There you go.

303
00:38:37,940 --> 00:38:40,300
Ah, let's get the hell out of here.

304
00:39:39,745 --> 00:39:42,065
Carter!
Carter, wait!

305
00:39:53,065 --> 00:39:55,345
She's flagging us down.

306
00:39:55,865 --> 00:39:58,787
- What's wrong?
- They shouldn't leave.

307
00:40:00,707 --> 00:40:02,147
Carter.

308
00:40:02,467 --> 00:40:04,227
Let's just get out of here, man.

309
00:40:11,387 --> 00:40:13,107
Alright, fuck it, we're landing.

310
00:40:13,187 --> 00:40:14,507
Shit.

311
00:40:14,587 --> 00:40:16,188
Let's take her down.

312
00:40:18,948 --> 00:40:20,588
Is there something wrong?

313
00:40:21,988 --> 00:40:23,748
No, everything's fine.

314
00:40:30,388 --> 00:40:32,108
Probably just forgot something.

315
00:40:33,108 --> 00:40:35,669
We'll be in the air in no time, okay?

316
00:40:36,909 --> 00:40:38,709
Don't worry.

317
00:40:38,949 --> 00:40:40,709
Hang in there.

318
00:41:00,231 --> 00:41:01,831
Something's wrong.

319
00:41:29,383 --> 00:41:32,713
Hailing McMurdo, or any ears on
the emergency channel.

320
00:41:32,873 --> 00:41:35,033
Do you copy? Over.

321
00:41:36,733 --> 00:41:39,293
I repeat, this is Thule Station.

322
00:41:39,613 --> 00:41:42,793
They crashed here,
right behind this ridgeline.

323
00:41:45,623 --> 00:41:47,115
It's impossible to reach them.

324
00:41:49,065 --> 00:41:51,155
This doesn't make any sense.

325
00:41:51,435 --> 00:41:53,745
I mean, they have plenty
of visibility, right?

326
00:41:53,805 --> 00:41:56,255
We're not going after them?
Shouldn't we try?

327
00:41:56,295 --> 00:41:58,395
We need a chopper
to even get close to them.

328
00:41:58,525 --> 00:42:00,055
And there's refueling and hailing.

329
00:42:01,075 --> 00:42:03,395
All this can't be a coincidence.

330
00:42:05,396 --> 00:42:08,516
Radio's dead. It's fucking dead.

331
00:42:10,036 --> 00:42:11,636
The incoming storm.

332
00:42:11,716 --> 00:42:12,956
Fuck.

333
00:42:13,076 --> 00:42:14,596
There's too much interference.

334
00:42:40,917 --> 00:42:44,639
We have four missing persons.
We have no helicopter or radio.

335
00:42:44,759 --> 00:42:48,759
You made a mistake
for bringing these people here.

336
00:42:48,839 --> 00:42:50,239
More people may die.

337
00:42:50,359 --> 00:42:53,039
But, Sander, we don't know
even if they are dead or not.

338
00:42:53,359 --> 00:42:56,239
Colin, Lars, get your gear.

339
00:42:58,119 --> 00:43:00,039
<i>We'll take a snowcat
to the next base.</i>

340
00:43:00,119 --> 00:43:01,520
Lars, do it now.

341
00:43:02,600 --> 00:43:04,320
I don't think that's a good idea.

342
00:43:06,840 --> 00:43:08,200
And why is that?

343
00:43:08,480 --> 00:43:10,560
Because no one can leave this camp...

344
00:43:10,680 --> 00:43:12,760
until we know more about
what's going on here.

345
00:43:12,840 --> 00:43:15,320
- I make decisions about this camp.
- I know, Edvard, but...

346
00:43:15,440 --> 00:43:17,160
Why did you flag down that helicopter?

347
00:43:17,240 --> 00:43:18,921
Because I thought it was in danger.

348
00:43:19,001 --> 00:43:20,321
Why?

349
00:43:21,161 --> 00:43:23,401
I took a sample of Henrik's blood...

350
00:43:23,801 --> 00:43:26,081
and I saw that the alien cells
were still alive.

351
00:43:26,201 --> 00:43:29,681
They were alive and they were copying
Henrik's cells.

352
00:43:30,281 --> 00:43:32,201
Replicating them.

353
00:43:33,681 --> 00:43:35,121
Adam saw it too.

354
00:43:37,843 --> 00:43:39,123
Is that true?

355
00:43:41,883 --> 00:43:43,203
I don't know.

356
00:43:43,523 --> 00:43:45,523
I mean, I don't know what we saw.

357
00:43:45,603 --> 00:43:47,603
I mean, we saw something.

358
00:43:47,723 --> 00:43:50,123
I don't understand.
What are you saying?

359
00:43:52,923 --> 00:43:57,124
That this thing can,
and probably has,

360
00:43:57,204 --> 00:43:59,084
replicated a person.

361
00:43:59,204 --> 00:44:00,884
- What?
- That can't be.

362
00:44:00,964 --> 00:44:02,564
- Who?
- This is insane.

363
00:44:02,684 --> 00:44:05,604
Okay, Okay. Kate? Kate?
Okay! Kate.

364
00:44:06,404 --> 00:44:08,564
This is not the time to be yelling fire.

365
00:44:08,964 --> 00:44:11,764
Let's stop, gather our thoughts,

366
00:44:11,884 --> 00:44:13,604
and discuss this in private.

367
00:44:13,685 --> 00:44:15,845
We don't need
any private meeting, Doctor.

368
00:44:15,925 --> 00:44:17,325
We all want the fucking information!

369
00:44:17,445 --> 00:44:18,845
There's more.

370
00:44:21,325 --> 00:44:22,565
What are those?

371
00:44:22,685 --> 00:44:25,285
I think they are fillings
from someone's teeth.

372
00:44:25,525 --> 00:44:27,805
I found them by a puddle of blood
in the shower.

373
00:44:27,925 --> 00:44:29,165
Puddle of blood?

374
00:44:29,285 --> 00:44:31,685
It can clone cells,
but not inorganic material.

375
00:44:31,765 --> 00:44:34,847
It couldn't copy these, so
it spit them out.

376
00:44:35,907 --> 00:44:37,807
We're wasting too much time already.
Lars?

377
00:44:37,808 --> 00:44:38,708
Listen!

378
00:44:39,527 --> 00:44:43,167
When I went back to check it,
someone had cleaned up the blood.

379
00:44:43,607 --> 00:44:45,407
Someone had wiped it away.

380
00:44:46,447 --> 00:44:48,687
Alright, so whatever it is...

381
00:44:49,527 --> 00:44:52,048
It is still here.

382
00:44:57,608 --> 00:44:59,088
I've heard enough.

383
00:44:59,608 --> 00:45:02,288
Lars, Colin, get the gear.
Ten minutes.

384
00:45:03,688 --> 00:45:05,268
Please, Edvard.

385
00:45:05,988 --> 00:45:06,968
You can't leave.

386
00:45:07,948 --> 00:45:10,509
You can't leave!
You don't know what we're dealing with.

387
00:45:14,569 --> 00:45:15,569
Well done.

388
00:45:25,739 --> 00:45:26,631
Kate?

389
00:45:31,011 --> 00:45:33,471
I don't know
if I should be speaking about this.

390
00:45:33,991 --> 00:45:35,531
I don't want to get anyone in trouble.

391
00:45:35,611 --> 00:45:36,651
Speaking about what?

392
00:45:37,471 --> 00:45:38,691
You were saying...

393
00:45:39,391 --> 00:45:42,711
about someone cleaning up the
blood from the shower.

394
00:45:42,891 --> 00:45:44,872
And that someone here
may not be themselves.

395
00:45:44,873 --> 00:45:45,973
Juliette, please...

396
00:45:47,652 --> 00:45:48,932
What did you see?

397
00:45:50,092 --> 00:45:56,072
After the crash, I think... I saw
Colin coming from the showers.

398
00:45:56,192 --> 00:45:57,792
He was holding something.

399
00:45:58,572 --> 00:46:02,012
It could've been a towel, a rag,
something to clean up.

400
00:46:02,732 --> 00:46:07,333
Kate, I can't say for sure, but
it's just that I s...

401
00:46:22,815 --> 00:46:24,275
He's leaving with Edvard.

402
00:46:24,395 --> 00:46:25,895
We can't let them go.

403
00:46:26,615 --> 00:46:27,955
We can't let any of them go.

404
00:46:29,595 --> 00:46:32,255
I know where they keep
the keys for the vehicles.

405
00:46:39,675 --> 00:46:42,196
- Where are they?
- In that drawer.

406
00:46:43,496 --> 00:46:45,176
- This one?
- Yes.

407
00:46:48,956 --> 00:46:52,256
- How many am I looking for?
- Five.

408
00:46:53,996 --> 00:46:55,436
Three and four.

409
00:46:57,056 --> 00:46:58,357
You said there were five?

410
00:47:34,499 --> 00:47:35,760
Run!

411
00:47:46,260 --> 00:47:47,500
Kate, what happened?

412
00:47:48,380 --> 00:47:51,660
Karl. It got Karl.
It got... Karl.

413
00:48:10,701 --> 00:48:11,981
Kate.

414
00:48:24,623 --> 00:48:25,983
Burn it!

415
00:49:26,508 --> 00:49:28,508
Enough, that's enough.

416
00:49:30,868 --> 00:49:32,788
Burn in hell.

417
00:49:49,669 --> 00:49:51,589
What the fuck's happening to us?

418
00:49:57,909 --> 00:49:59,749
It attacks its prey,

419
00:50:01,149 --> 00:50:03,191
copies it perfectly...

420
00:50:03,911 --> 00:50:05,791
and then hides inside it.

421
00:50:06,711 --> 00:50:08,151
Waiting.

422
00:50:10,871 --> 00:50:12,671
Is it still among us?

423
00:50:15,751 --> 00:50:17,471
It could be any of us.

424
00:50:23,312 --> 00:50:25,072
We got to get out of here.

425
00:50:25,192 --> 00:50:26,712
Yeah, right now.

426
00:50:26,792 --> 00:50:29,352
And it could be getting
a vehicle with it.

427
00:50:30,752 --> 00:50:32,552
You'll be alone.

428
00:50:33,072 --> 00:50:34,592
Vulnerable.

429
00:50:36,512 --> 00:50:38,592
That's exactly what it wants.

430
00:50:39,833 --> 00:50:42,673
Not to mention you'll be giving it
a way out of here.

431
00:50:43,313 --> 00:50:45,193
A way to spread.

432
00:50:46,873 --> 00:50:48,713
It's like a virus.

433
00:50:49,513 --> 00:50:51,513
So what do we do with any virus?

434
00:50:51,833 --> 00:50:53,433
Quarantine.

435
00:50:54,713 --> 00:50:58,235
We isolate it and then we kill it.

436
00:50:59,355 --> 00:51:00,715
Yeah.

437
00:51:01,475 --> 00:51:03,715
We have to rely on science.

438
00:51:04,035 --> 00:51:07,235
Exposing our uncontaminated blood to the
cells of the creature

439
00:51:07,355 --> 00:51:10,355
might create a reaction...
of some kind.

440
00:51:10,435 --> 00:51:12,835
So we take blood samples from everybody.

441
00:51:13,235 --> 00:51:15,395
Yeah, and we test each one of them.

442
00:51:15,916 --> 00:51:18,316
Yes, Adam and I can do that.

443
00:51:19,996 --> 00:51:21,276
Okay.

444
00:51:23,356 --> 00:51:25,396
Lars and I'll disable the vehicles.

445
00:51:27,396 --> 00:51:29,476
We have to trust in this plan.

446
00:51:32,796 --> 00:51:35,277
It's our only chance
of making it through this.

447
00:51:51,077 --> 00:51:52,839
- Is that it?
- Yes.

448
00:51:53,239 --> 00:51:55,599
- No more vehicles?
- Only these.

449
00:51:56,079 --> 00:51:57,319
Okay.

450
00:52:06,439 --> 00:52:07,879
What?

451
00:52:32,921 --> 00:52:34,361
Grenades.

452
00:52:44,121 --> 00:52:46,121
Is everything alright?

453
00:52:51,403 --> 00:52:53,683
Yes, yes, everything's fine.

454
00:52:55,763 --> 00:52:57,043
Good.

455
00:52:58,763 --> 00:53:00,963
- Lars, you're okay?
- Yes.

456
00:53:01,083 --> 00:53:02,923
Kate, we should go.

457
00:53:03,483 --> 00:53:05,243
The storm is getting worse.

458
00:53:20,404 --> 00:53:21,844
Who is that?

459
00:53:33,685 --> 00:53:35,445
Hurry up. They're coming.

460
00:53:48,887 --> 00:53:50,607
The Americans.

461
00:53:53,687 --> 00:53:56,687
It is impossible for a human
to survive in that crash.

462
00:53:58,087 --> 00:54:01,848
We should burn them.
Right here, right now.

463
00:54:02,688 --> 00:54:04,848
- Let's finish them off!
- Peder?

464
00:54:05,728 --> 00:54:07,328
It could be murder.

465
00:54:07,408 --> 00:54:10,528
- It could be survival, Kate.
- Yes, but we don't have to kill them.

466
00:54:10,648 --> 00:54:12,928
Right? We can just lock them up...

467
00:54:13,048 --> 00:54:15,248
until the Sander's test is ready.

468
00:54:15,888 --> 00:54:17,408
Please.

469
00:54:18,969 --> 00:54:20,409
Please.

470
00:55:12,972 --> 00:55:14,513
So this is a good idea?

471
00:55:17,093 --> 00:55:18,453
Locking us up?

472
00:55:21,873 --> 00:55:23,333
You need our help.

473
00:55:40,055 --> 00:55:43,135
Warn your scientists they can't handle
with what we saw in that chopper.

474
00:55:44,715 --> 00:55:46,675
For all I know,
you could be one of those things.

475
00:55:48,635 --> 00:55:51,055
It's pretty hard to believe
you both walked away from that crash.

476
00:55:51,375 --> 00:55:54,196
- Yeah, I get that, I do, but...
- We're preparing a test.

477
00:55:56,556 --> 00:55:57,936
And then we figure out who's who.

478
00:55:59,696 --> 00:56:01,176
It's all I can offer you right now.

479
00:56:45,520 --> 00:56:47,520
Damn!
There's a fire here!

480
00:57:04,961 --> 00:57:07,881
Someone sabotaged it.
There's nothing left. Nothing.

481
00:57:08,261 --> 00:57:09,581
Now there's no test.

482
00:57:10,761 --> 00:57:11,921
How could this happen?

483
00:57:12,641 --> 00:57:13,941
It was no accident.

484
00:57:15,061 --> 00:57:15,981
You.

485
00:57:17,261 --> 00:57:18,581
You were in there with him.

486
00:57:19,201 --> 00:57:20,581
You were the last one.

487
00:57:20,901 --> 00:57:23,023
- How are you accusing me?
- Why not?

488
00:57:23,943 --> 00:57:26,103
- He's got something to hide.
- What are you, an asshole?

489
00:57:26,283 --> 00:57:28,523
I was the one working on the test.
I left for 2 minutes!

490
00:57:28,603 --> 00:57:29,763
You just don't want us
to know the truth,

491
00:57:29,764 --> 00:57:31,064
- do ya?
- Bullshit!

492
00:57:31,153 --> 00:57:33,893
This is a goddamn fucking nightmare!

493
00:57:34,163 --> 00:57:35,363
There might be another way.

494
00:57:39,663 --> 00:57:43,784
I think there might be...
another way to tell.

495
00:58:00,025 --> 00:58:01,305
Peder, give me your flashlight.

496
00:58:06,625 --> 00:58:08,625
Now tell Lars...
to open his mouth.

497
00:58:09,845 --> 00:58:11,005
Tell him to open his mouth.

498
00:58:15,245 --> 00:58:16,767
Open your mouth.

499
00:58:24,287 --> 00:58:25,927
That's good.

500
00:58:26,367 --> 00:58:29,407
Lars has fillings.
So he's human.

501
00:58:29,487 --> 00:58:31,607
It can't imitate
inorganic material.

502
00:58:32,827 --> 00:58:34,187
See?

503
00:58:35,627 --> 00:58:36,948
Yes.

504
00:58:46,588 --> 00:58:47,908
Good.

505
00:58:48,908 --> 00:58:50,428
Good.

506
00:58:52,228 --> 00:58:53,628
Open.

507
00:58:54,229 --> 00:58:55,629
Come on!

508
00:58:56,629 --> 00:58:58,269
You're next!

509
00:58:58,349 --> 00:59:00,069
Open your mouth!

510
00:59:07,509 --> 00:59:08,669
Okay.

511
00:59:10,189 --> 00:59:11,829
Good.

512
00:59:15,591 --> 00:59:17,711
Right now, it's at least something.

513
00:59:18,751 --> 00:59:20,511
A way to eliminate
some of us.

514
00:59:20,591 --> 00:59:22,871
So I'm gonna get killed because
I floss?

515
00:59:22,991 --> 00:59:24,871
Nobody's getting killed.

516
00:59:25,191 --> 00:59:26,471
Kate?

517
00:59:26,591 --> 00:59:29,351
Kate, come on.

518
00:59:29,711 --> 00:59:31,112
Kate.

519
00:59:32,912 --> 00:59:34,352
Just do it.

520
00:59:34,952 --> 00:59:36,212
Kate.

521
00:59:39,272 --> 00:59:40,412
Open.

